AFTER DAYS of mounting pressure–sparked by a scandal involving his deputy chief whip–Britain’s prime minister quit as Conservative Party leader. The scandal is one of many that plagued his leadership, but the problems facing the Tories run far deeper. Host Anne McElvoy asks The Economist’s Andrew Palmer and Soumaya Keynes what brought the curtain down on Mr Johnson and what problems await his successor. Plus, Charles Powell, Margaret Thatcher’s closest adviser, assesses the similarities between the denouement of the two charismatic and controversial leaders. Runtime: 34 min  Please subscribe to The Economist for full access to print, digital and audio editions: www.economist.com/podcastoffer Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn